2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 10
BY SENATOR FOIL
CONDOLENCES. Expresses sincere and heartfelt condolences to the family and friends of
David Arnold Trusty on the occasion of his passing.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To express the sincere condolences of the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana upon the
3 death of David Arnold Trusty and to honor his life and legacy.
4 WHEREAS, it is with profound sorrow that the Senate of the Legislature of
5 Louisiana has learned of the passing of David Arnold Trusty on Tuesday, July 29, 2025, at
6 the age of seventy-one; and
7 WHEREAS, David was a longtime resident of Baton Rouge and a highly respected
8 real estate broker whose vision and leadership were instrumental in the development of
9 numerous projects throughout the Baton Rouge area; and
10 WHEREAS, he enjoyed a distinguished career spanning more than two decades in
11 sales and broadcasting management, with his journey beginning in Hawaii and continuing
12 throughout the southern United States; ultimately bringing him to Baton Rouge; and
13 WHEREAS, he spent many years with Clear Channel Broadcasting, iHeartRadio,
14 mentoring countless sales professionals and forming lifelong friendships; and
15 WHEREAS, real estate became his passion after joining Gully, Phelps &
16 McKey/Coldwell Banker in 2005, and in 2019 he founded Trusty Investment Properties,
17 LLC-Trusty Commercial with his son, John, later joined by his daughter, Lauren, in 2020
18 to lead the residential division; and
