1 WHEREAS, David was admired not only for his professional accomplishments but
2 also for his warmth, integrity, infectious smile, generous spirit, affection for pocket squares,
3 and zest for life; and
4 WHEREAS, he was known for his love of cooking, fine wine, and time spent with
5 family and friends; always accompanied by his Golden Retriever, Charlie; and
6 WHEREAS, David leaves behind a legacy of love, wisdom, and devotion to his
7 family and friends; he is survived by his beloved wife of thirty-eight years, Renee; his
8 children, Lauren and John; cherished grandchildren, Calum, Ford, Kingston, and Grace; his
9 mother, Pauleen; his siblings, and a wide circle of extended family, friends, and community
10 members; and
11 WHEREAS, David Arnold Trusty's life exemplified hard work, excellence, kindness,
12 and an abiding love for life, coupled with unwavering dedication to his family and
13 community, and his legacy will endure in the hearts of all who were touched by his presence.
14 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
15 does hereby extend its sincere and heartfelt condolences to the family and friends of David
16 Arnold Trusty.
17 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
18 family of David Arnold Trusty.
